  <entry>
    <id>tag:www.gov.uk,2005:PublicationesquePresenter/11311</id>
    <published>2012-04-02T00:00:00+01:00</published>
    <updated>2012-04-02T00:00:00+01:00</updated>
    <link rel="alternate" type="text/html" href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/changes-to-the-energy-performance-of-buildings-framework"/>
    <title>Changes to the energy performance of buildings framework</title>
    <content type="html">&lt;div class="govspeak"&gt;&lt;p&gt;The documents below describe the April 2012 changes to the Energy Performance of Buildings framework.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We have taken steps to make it easier for consumers to save money on their fuel bills by:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;introducing a new look domestic Energy Performance Certificate which is consumer friendly and easy to understand&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;requiring Domestic Energy Assessors to improve their skills and deliver a better customer service&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;opening up access to the Energy Performance Certificate register of more than seven million Energy Performance Certificates&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;amending the Regulations so the Energy Performance Certificate is provided earlier to prospective buyers and tenants, increasing the likelihood of people acting on recommendations which identify cost effective savings.&lt;/li&gt;
